_aLatestUpdates._sText: This is the full release of zm_london

_sText:
zm\_london by Soft Serve (a.k.a. Satin Storm)

Features:

- Above ground: city streets, market, pub, night club, and several small interiors.
- Below ground: laboratory, sewers, train depot, and many tunnels leading to various places.
- Three special items: kryptonite (T), gas mask (CT), and Superman (CT)!
- Many hiding spots suitable for both limited and unlimited ammo servers.
- Several secret teleporters, buttons, coded rooms, and other hidden areas.

---

Special item info:

- Gas mask (Human, Deagle): Allows user to survive the airlock cycle in the ventilation shafts. Passive.
- Superman (Human, P90): Enables user to fly and run quickly. Passive.
- Kryptonite (Zombie, Knife): Slows down and removes Superman's ability to fly for 30 seconds. Infinite uses. 60 second cooldown.

---

Version history:

v1_0 (FULL RELEASE)

- Added soundscapes
- Added colour correction
- Adjusted fog colour
- Changed some lighting
- Added new store interior
- Added path to secret sewer area
- Coffee shop windows are now breakable
- Changed/added/removed props throughout the map
- Added underground garage/loading bay
- Moved kryptonite to a more obvious location
- Added security booth next to coded gate for easier entry
- Added ladder from sewer to underground complex
- Moved balcony teleporters
- Made most doors toggle instead of slam shut
- Added another underground teleporter to the streets
- Added small side room to lab
- Kryptonite zombie now gets 10000 health
- Lab doors now open/close faster
- Sewer manhole is now easier to enter
- Fixed spot on roof where it was possible to get stuck as Superman

v0_3 (not released on GB)

- Buffed kryptonite
- Various small fixes and balance tweaks

v0_2

- First public release.

v0_1

- Private beta.

This is a remake of zm_lila_panic. The two primary features are that it is retextured and has superior lighting. The textures used are all dust textures, which means you can choose new textures for the map from FPSB's wonderful assortment of de_dust & de_dust2 retextures. http://www.fpsbanana.com/skins/49064 Another feature of this map is that it was designed to have NO cheap/illegal spots on it. This means that it can be played on servers with the tightest camping restrictions. There are no tubes, vents, crouch spots, or high spots that players can camp on that are unfair to zombies. If you think a spot is cheap, think again - there is a very simple but secret way to get there. (Btw that doesn't mean there are no places to camp, there are still plenty of rooms to barricade and plenty of places outside to camp on. This map has many secrets to be discovered - but be careful, some of them are deadly. Please...DO NOT ASK ME FOR THE PASSCODE! I will NOT tell you the passcode, and please DO NOT try and decompile the map because it is decompile-protected. Also note that the first 5 screenshots are with retextured de_dust textures - the last screenshot shows the map with default textures. Not as good looking, I know. Check out this reskin: http://www.fpsbanana.com/skins/49064 There is only one known bug with this version. Some players manage to fall off the map somehow. I have tried with many past versions to correct this, but it never seems to work.

If you like or use my
map please rate! ty.

Misc info: no HDR (sorry, I did try to add it though). Nav included. map is 7.75M, nav is 233K, total download is 1.6M. Enjoy ^_^

This map took a while to re-do. Yes, I know, it's been re-done like a million times but it's a very popular map, and I had to make a remake for my clan. I've added a lot since the normal. I've taken out the tubes so no more tube camping, I've made realistic roofs and made all doors the correct sizes. I've added as much as I could to increase fps, but still in some spots it's still not the best. I've added some better looking stairs, and added a sun. There is one secret room, but I can't tell where ;) Please don't just say "eh, it's another remake," try it for yourself!
